parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause serious injury or death, and may lead to a total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: Engine fires
oil leaks
smoke coming from under the hood
oil spillage into the passenger compartment
hot and discolored wires in the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause engine failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Oil leaks can also cause engine compartment fires.
symptoms: Oil leaks
oil dumping from the engine
oil spillage into the passenger compartment
engine failure
smoke coming from the exhaust system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uncompleted recalls can lead to serious safety issues, such as engine compartment fires, oil leaks, and engine failure.
symptoms: Uncompleted recalls
lack of notification from the manufacturer or dealer
refusal of the manufacturer or dealer to perform the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust system issues can cause engine failure, oil leaks, and smoke coming from the exhaust system.
symptoms: Oil getting into the exhaust system
smoke coming from the exhaust system
oil spillage into the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A non-functional parking brake adjuster can cause the parking brake to fail, leading to unintended vehicle movement, accidents, or injuries, especially when parked on an incline.
symptoms: The parking brake does not engage or disengage properly
the vehicle rolls or moves when parked on an incline
the emergency brake does not hold the vehicle in place
the vehicle does not pass state inspection due to parking brake issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake calipers can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear brake calipers are frozen solid
the rear brakes do not function properly
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brakes make unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty rear brake adjustment system can lead to premature wear of the brake components, causing the rear brakes to fail, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The rear brakes require frequent adjustments
the rear brake pads wear down unevenly
the rear brake calipers are difficult to adjust
the rear brake system makes unusual noises or vibrations.
